         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne Botanic Garden, 23rd March 1873. ¶ Sir ¶ , ¶  ¶ In reply to your communication, just received, I have the honor to inform you that the weeds of which you transmit a sample, is botanically kn...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">73.03.23b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To John Kerr</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found; for the text given here, see B73.07.01, p. 51. Although M addressed his letter to the Chief Inspector of Sheep, other letters published with it are directed to or written by the Acting Chief Inspector of <seg style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">Stock</hi>
                     </seg>, John Kerr.</p>
               </note>Melbourne Botanic Garden, 23rd March 1873.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">Sir</seg>,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In reply to your communication, just received, I have the honor to inform you that the weeds of which you transmit a sample, is botanically known as <name key="Lobelia%20pratioides">Lobelia pratioides</name>, and belongs to a genus of highly poisonous plants. Hence I have no doubt that the death of the cattle at Geelong, Maidstone, and Braybrook<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>All in Vic.</p>
               </note> is to be traced to the prevalence of this herb at this season on spots very bare of pastoral vegetation. The best means for setting this question at rest would be to administer the herb to a sheep or some other pastoral animal, and to watch whether the animal thus experimented on will succumb under the same symptoms which were manifested when the cattle at Geelong, &amp;c., expired.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I have, &amp;c.,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>(Signed) <seg style="text-transform: uppercase; ">Ferd. von Mueller</seg>,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Director of the Botanic Garden.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The Chief Inspector of Sheep.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Postscript</seg>. — I would advise that patches densely beset with the Lobelia, which is perennial, should be ploughed and then sown with the seeds of vigorously growing perennial grasses, clovers, luzern, &amp;c.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Lobelia%20pratioides">Lobelia pratioides</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
